# Documentation updates

Update docs in the **same PR** when behavior or contracts change.

## When to update

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New/changed API route | `docs/architecture/api-contract.md` |
| New tables/columns | `docs/architecture/overview.md` ER section + migration file |
| Schema changes | Follow `.cursor/rules/06-reuse-first.mdc` schema hard rule |
| Deploy behavior | `docs/architecture/deploy.md` |
| Significant technical choice | New `docs/decisions/ADR-NNNN-*.md` |
| Feature milestone | `docs/milestones/<slug>.md` + README index（结构见 `_TEMPLATE.md`） |
| User-visible feature or behavior change | Root `README.md`「功能」一节（同 PR） |
| Doc hub / onboarding | `docs/README.md`, `docs/GETTING-START.md`, `docs/ai-playbook.md` |
| Ops guides | `docs/ops/` |

## ADR format

Use `docs/decisions/_template.md`. Keep ADRs short: context, decision, consequences.

## Milestone lifecycle

When a milestone's acceptance criteria are all met:

1. Change `Status: active` → `Status: done` in `docs/milestones/<slug>.md`.
2. Update the row in `docs/milestones/README.md` to `done`.
3. Commit the status change in the same PR as the feature, or as a follow-up `docs:` commit.

## Do not

- Put secrets in docs or committed `.env` files
